+    Top level `val` properties and `const val` properties have to be written in screaming snake notation. Local `val` and `const val` are written in lower camel case. However, mutable collection properties (such as `MutableMap`, `MutableList`, `MutableSet`, `MutableCollection`) use camelCase naming even when declared in objects, following the Android Kotlin Style Guide.
 
